Description: temporary SSH access broker and CLI
 SSHFling grants short-lived SSH access with default password grants,
 optional OpenSSH user certificates, and a forced session wrapper so
 temporary SSH sessions are capped by a server-side wall-clock timeout.
 Docker Compose files are included as a test harness.
 .
 This draft source package is not ready for official Debian or Ubuntu
 upload while the upstream license remains proprietary and
 redistribution-restricted.
